'''The Philosophical Library''' (Philosophical and Religious Free Library<ref>Pat Sherman (2005)</ref>) is a non-profit organization run entirely by volunteers and founded in 1963. It administers extensive lending privileges in a wide array of books in the fields of [[philosophy]], [[religion]], [[metaphysics]] and [[spiritual practices]]. It presents itself as a "place of fellowship and spiritual growth as well as a research and study center." The Philosophical Library's [[mission statement]]: "Our mission at The Philosophical Library is to create a Conscious Community by providing unique resources for those seeking meaning through diverse paths of Wisdom."
